            "text": " where  $p$  and  $q$  are the XAS intensity differences  $(I_{left} - I_{right})$  integrated over the  $L_3$  edge and the entire  $L_{2,3}$  region, respectively (Fig. 6). The XAS intensity  $I$ , after background correction (sec. S.V-A), is integrated over  $L_{2,3}$  to yield  $r$ .  $\\langle T_z \\rangle$  is the expectation value of the intra-atomic magnetic dipole operator which is  $-0.0002\\hbar$  and hence negligible (sec. S.V-A). For  $n_d$  we use the MLFT value of 5.31 (sec. II E). Finally,  $C$  is a correction factor, which takes into account the considerable overlap of the  $L_3$  and  $L_2$  contributions for light transition metals. We use a value of  $C = 1.4$  (sec. S.V-A). To circumvent the difficulties related to this overlap, one can obtain  $m_{XM}^{spin}$  by a comparison of the experimental XMCD asymmetry at the  $L_3$  peak to the theoretical one calculated from MLFT spectra of comparable line width [\\[52–54\\]](#page-).V. ",
