            "text": " The raw XAS spectra were scaled with respect to each other to have the same intensity at energies far from the resonances to obtain  $I_{left}$  and  $I_{right}$ . We define the XMCD signal as  $I_{XMCD} = I_{left} - I_{right}$ . The average, not background corrected XAS is  $I = (I_{left} + I_{right})/2$ . To cancel out any experimental drifts, for each data set we measured eight spectra in a row by altering the X-ray polarization. Finally, the magnetic moments measured with XMCD are marked with the subscript XM, e. g.  $m_{XM}^{tot}$ .",
